{
  "analysis": "The terminal output was interleaved because the exact brute-force search was still printing while later commands were queued. We have a known valid 2-byte stream, `4f 02`, that decompresses to `01`, but our generated non-empty streams are invalid. The next needed evidence is clean diagnostics for the known-good stream and our generated stream to identify the arithmetic encoder bug.",
  "plan": "Poll/stabilize the shell with a marker command. Then run a compact diagnostic for the known-good `4f 02` stream and our generated `/app/t1.comp` using the existing decsim with clear separators. This should show the decoded token count/tokens for good versus bad streams.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "echo STABLE_PROMPT\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "printf '\\x4f\\x02' > /tmp/good.bin && echo \"GOOD_BYTES\" && od -An -tx1 -v /tmp/good.bin && echo \"GOOD_DECOMP\" && cat /tmp/good.bin | /app/decomp | od -An -tx1 -v && echo \"GOOD_DECSIM\" && cat /tmp/good.bin | /app/decsim > /tmp/good.out 2>/tmp/good.err; head -20 /tmp/good.err; echo \"GOOD_OUT\"; od -An -tx1 -v /tmp/good.out\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "echo \"T1_BYTES\" && od -An -tx1 -v /app/t1.comp && echo \"T1_DECSIM\" && cat /app/t1.comp | /app/decsim > /tmp/t1.out 2>/tmp/t1.err; head -20 /tmp/t1.err; echo \"T1_OUT\"; od -An -tx1 -v /tmp/t1.out\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    }
  ]
}
